original: Carling, Carl Birger, länsassessor, Linköping, f. 21/10/01 i Norrköp. av byggnichefen Willgott C. o. Agnes Enequist. G. 32 m. Märta Lindquist. ’ Barn: Margareta f. 43. — Stud:ex. i Norrköp. 20, jur. kand. i Upps. 27. Tingstjg. 27-29, e. befattnihav. å landskont. i Jönköp. 1. 30, e. o. läns-bokhåll. 33, tf. dito av 2. kl. i Öster-götl. 1. 38, konstitutorial å denna tjänst 43, länsbokhåll. av 1. kl. 44, länsassessor sed. 46.
translated: Carling, Carl Birger, county assessor, Linköping, born October 21, 1901, in Norrköping, to the building chief Willgott C. and Agnes Enequist. Married in 1932 to Märta Lindquist. They had one child, Margareta, born in 1943. Carl Birger obtained his high school diploma in Norrköping in 1920 and a law degree in Uppsala in 1927. He served as an associate judge from 1927 to 1929, held a position at the county office in Jönköping from 1930, was an acting county accountant in Östergötland from 1933, and was appointed county accountant in 1944. He became county assessor in 1946.
